results.name: Where n appears in A111267.
link: Donovan Johnson, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..2000
maple: INVERSE := proc(a) local b,c,i,n,hit,ulim; if whattype(a) <> list then RETURN([]); fi: c:=sort(a); b:=[]; ulim:=min(1000,c[nops(c)]); for n from c[1] to ulim do hit:=0; for i from 1 to nops(a) do if a[i]=n then b:=[op(b),i]; hit:=1; break; fi; od; if hit = 0 then RETURN(b); fi; od; end:
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, Nov 03 2005
